TLSformer on bulk RNA-seq

2024-05-27

Pred bulk RNA-seq data

This is an demo show how to use TLSformertarget training on spatial transcriptomics data to pred TCGA bulk-RNA tissue

Read data

# spatial data
st_dat_train <- readRDS("/home/xfan/MLTLS_package/demo_data/bc_st_demo_data.rds")

# bulk data
bulk_dat_pred <- data.table::fread("/home/xfan/TCGA-BRCA_exp.txt") %>%
    as.data.frame() %>%
    column_to_rownames(var = "Array") %>%
    t() %>%
    as.data.frame()

# intersect genes of spatial data, bulk data, and pre-trained gene word encoder
gene_intersect <- data.table::fread("/home/xfan/MLTLS_package/demo_data/pretrained_models_rank260/genelist.txt") %>%
  as.data.frame()
gene_intersect <- gene_intersect$Gene
gene_intersect <- intersect(gene_intersect,rownames(st_dat_train@assays$Spatial@counts))
gene_intersect <- intersect(gene_intersect,rownames(bulk_dat_pred))
gene_intersect <- as.data.frame(gene_intersect)
colnames(gene_intersect) <- "Gene"
write.table(gene_intersect,file = "/home/xfan/MLTLS_package/demo_data/pretrained_models_rank260/genelist_intersect.txt",sep = "\t",quote = F,col.names = T,row.names = F)

Survival analysis

library(survival)
library(survminer)

os_dat <- as.data.frame(t(bulk_dat_pred[c("OS","OS.Event"),]))
os_dat$OS <- as.numeric(os_dat$OS)
os_dat$OS.Event <- as.numeric(os_dat$OS.Event)
os_dat <- cbind(os_dat[rownames(bulk_dat_pred_results),],bulk_dat_pred_results)
os_dat$threshold <- ifelse(os_dat$relative_distance>=median(os_dat$relative_distance),"low","high")
fit <- survfit(Surv(OS,OS.Event)~threshold,data = os_dat)
diff <- survdiff(Surv(OS,OS.Event)~threshold,data = os_dat)
pvalue <- round(1 - pchisq(diff$chisq,df = 1), 3)
HR = (diff$obs[1]/diff$exp[1])/(diff$obs[2]/diff$exp[2])
up95 = exp(log(HR) + qnorm(0.975)*sqrt(1/diff$exp[2]+1/diff$exp[1]))
low95 = exp(log(HR) - qnorm(0.975)*sqrt(1/diff$exp[2]+1/diff$exp[1]))

surPlot_bc = ggsurvplot(fit,
                        data=os_dat,
                        font.pval = c(size = 4.5, face = "italic", color = "black"),
                        pval.coord = c(3,0.15),
                        legend.labs=paste(levels(factor(os_dat$threshold))),
                        palette =  c("#DC2819","#4d4e75"),
                        legend = c(0.3,0.09),
                        size = 1.5,
                        font.x = 16,
                        font.y = 16,
                        conf.int = FALSE,
                        font.legend = list(size = 14, color = "black"),
                        xlab="Time(Days)",
                        ylab="Surivial Probability",
                        font.tickslab = c(12,"plain"),
                        break.time.by = 720,
                        risk.table.title="",
                        risk.table=F,     
                        risk.table.height=.25,
                        risk.table.y.text = F, 
                        ggtheme = theme_test())

surPlot_bc$plot <- surPlot_bc$plot +
      ggplot2::annotate(
        "text",
        x = Inf, y = Inf,
        vjust = 1, hjust = 1,
        label = paste0("pvalue:",pvalue,"\n","HR = ",round(HR,digits = 2)," (CI ",round(low95,digits = 2)," - ",round(up95,digits = 2),")"),
        size = 5
      ) +
      theme(legend.title=element_blank())
